  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Chest/abdominal wall varices and spider nevi are two common presenting signs of liver
      cirrhosis. Their prognostic values remain unclear.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <overall_status>Completed</overall_status>
  <start_date>June 2015</start_date>
